				Soulmate - Part 3
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Ah, there you are again my friends.  So you have come to listen to my ramblings again have you.  I see the brew master has brought us 6 of his finest.  What do you call that my friend?  A what?,  6-Pack&#8230;. Yes I can see why it is called a 6-Pack.  What is that other item our friend the Shaman is carrying?  It is round, made from dough and is topped with what looks like cheese, tomato sauce, and mushrooms.  No name for it yet, well when you have one let me know.  Can you put pixie wings on that thing as well as mushrooms? <br>  <br> I have entered my 9th season in Qeynos and the Black Burrow area.  I had problems until the other night and I would like to share with you my solution.  My healing powers did not increase with my 9th season but the amount of times I could heal did increase due to gaining more manna.  I did gain some additional spells that gave me some power; Root.  Yes, the spell Root that should hold any MOB in its grasp.  I envisioned rooting a putrid skeleton at the ruins and then hitting it with Ward Undead until it became a bag of bones.  Root, Nuke, Root what a lovely combination.  I am fully aware that I am slowly losing my ability to melee with our &#8220;unfriendly&#8221; MOBs in the lands and soon my Brass Mace will just be tickling them instead of bashing their brains out.  So, heading out to solo rabid wolfs and bears for experience was still an option to me but limited.  Crushing gnolls outside the entrance of Black Burrow for &#8220;gnoll fangs&#8221; was also slipping away since I was no longer getting experience for the deed.  Joining with fellow adventures in Black Burrow was becoming my only option or so I thought. <br>  <br> It happened while I was sitting under my favorite tree in front of Black Burrow.  I was meditating when the breeze began and my soulmate&#8217;s voice came to me again.  &#8220;Come East my love&#8221;.  I listened for more but that is all she said, or what I heard.  I did not know how far East she wanted me to go nor for what purpose.  I planned to practice root, nuke, root for a few days at the Qeynos Hills ruins but it looked like I had to put on my traveling robes and head East.  I was hoping to find a friend in Qeynos that could teleport me somewhere to the East to save me some days of travel, so I set out for Qeynos. <br>  <br> I was running up the valley towards the Guard Tower from Black Burrow when they hit.  Five Earth Elementals destroying everyone in their path.  It was carnage, nothing survived their wraith.  I spawned just outside the Gate of Qeynos and began to give the alarm as I was meditating and gathering my spells together.  I could hear shouts of &#8220;Earthquake&#8221; throughout the area and I again gave the warning of Elementals attacking.  They came into the zone 5 across,  friends of one and two seasons were massacred before my eyes and some brave souls stood their ground and began to fight the elementals and older friends ran like cowards.  I knew I would die again that day and threw myself into the fight.  I was casting healings and armor buffs as fast as I could until I was out of manna, then I would try to rest and start again.  Four times the Elementals descended upon me; and each time I thought it was a good day to die. <br>  <br> The last time I came back to Qeynos the fighting was over.  I do not know how they were defeated or if they even were, I just wandered the area and town looking at the dead.  There were scores of them, young and old.  Guards, storekeepers, and anyone else who was out in the open died.  Those inside buildings who survived the earthquakes were left alive.  I made an oath right then and there that if it was within my power that I would gather a force the next time the Elementals came and we would meet them at the gates to give them battle.  There will be many of us I promise you, and no one, no one, will run and hide on that day.  It grieved me and hurt me badly to see such carnage among our friends. <br>  <br> And so my friends here I am packing my bags and moving on to the East.  &#8220;Am I going alone they asked?&#8221;   With a twinkle in my eye I responded, &#8220;NO&#8221;, or at least I hope not.  Do not tell anyone, but I think &#8220;she&#8221; is here with me now.  I am going to ask her to come with me to the East.  If you care to walk with me a bit I will tell you about how we meet. <br>  <br> -------------------------------------------------- <br>  <br> Parts 1 and 2 can be found in earlier post. <br> -------------------------------------------------- <br> Gamthor - Lifegiver of the Lands .... <br> -------------------------------------------------- <br> Cleric casts &quot;Summon Pet&quot; ...... <br> Ranger Responds .................... <br> Group Formed ........................ <br> Killings Begin ......................... <br>  <br> 		

